IMPORTANT NOTES
============================================================

- If the feature folder does not exist, use New Feature.
- If the feature folder already exists, use Add to Existing Feature.
- In the first prompt, Copilot should only give the plan.
- In Phase 1, Phase 2, and Phase 3, Copilot should apply changes directly to files.
- Copilot should not paste full files in chat unless I explicitly ask for them.
- Always check compile errors after each phase before moving to the next phase.
- When copying a prompt to Copilot, copy only the text under the step title.
- Do not copy separator lines if you do not need them.
- Do not copy this whole file into Copilot every time.